# Testing

## Runner and environment

- Tests use **Vitest** with **jsdom** and root **`setupFiles`** / **`vitest.config.mts`** (see `docs/memory/techContext.md`).
- Use **`@excalidraw/*` path aliases** the same way as app code — do not bypass aliases with deep relative paths into `packages/` unless matching an existing test pattern.

## Snapshots

- Update snapshots only when the visual or serialized behavior change is intentional.
- Use **`yarn test:update`** (or the project’s documented test command) from the repo root after deliberate snapshot changes; do not commit flaky snapshot churn.

## Coverage and config

- Do not lower **`coverage.thresholds`** in `vitest.config.mts` without an explicit reason and review.
- Prefer fixing tests or code over disabling suites unless the skip is documented.

## Style

- Colocate tests as **`ComponentName.test.tsx`** next to components when that matches nearby files.
- Follow existing matchers and helpers from **`setupTests.ts`** and Testing Library usage in sibling tests.

## Disclose in chat

When this rule materially guides your response or edits, state in the Cursor chat that you applied it — mention `.cursor/rules/testing.mdc` (one short line is enough).

## How to verify

- From the repo root, run `yarn test:update` (or `yarn test:all` per `docs/memory/techContext.md`) before committing; snapshot diffs should match intentional behavior changes only.
- Confirm `vitest.config.mts` coverage thresholds and suite skips were not weakened without review.
